rican Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Insula","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Galician: habitational name from any of the places called Insua, meaning ‘island, peninsula (of a river or of the sea), land by a river’, from Latin <i>insula</i> ‘island’."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert de Insula was born in 1190, in Chesterton, Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Robert de Insula, was 26 and his mother, Beatrice de Cormeilles, was 25. He had at least 1 son with Sarah de Aunus. He died in 1223, in Cosford, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 33."},"et":{"1190–1223":"1190–1223","1195–1225":"1195–1225","1196–1221":"1196–1221","–Male":"Surnud","1164–Male":"1164–Surnud","1165–Female":"1165–Surnud","1190":"1190","1225":"1225","1223":"1223","1221":"1221","1165":"1165","1164":"1164","1196":"1196","before 5 October 1221":"enne 5. oktoobrit 1221","1195":"1195","Chesterton, Cambridgeshire, England":"Chesterton, Cambridgeshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Odell, Bedfordshire, England":"Odell, Bedfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Cosford, Suffolk, England":"Cosford, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1190–1223":"1190–1223","1195–1225":"1195–1225","1196–1221":"1196–1221","–Male":"Kuollut","1164–Male":"1164–Kuollut","1165–Female":"1165–Kuollut","1190":"1190","1225":"1225","1223":"1223","1221":"1221","1165":"1165","1164":"1164","1196":"1196","before 5 October 1221":"ennen vuotta 5. lokakuuta 1221","1195":"1195","Chesterton, Cambridgeshire, England":"Chesterton, Cambridgeshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Odell, Bedfordshire, England":"Odell, Bedfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Cosford, Suffolk, England":"Cosford, Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1190–1223":"1190–1223","1195–1225":"1195–1225","1196–1221":"1196–1221","–Male":"Décédé","1164–Male":"1164–Décédé","1165–Female":"1165–Décédée","1190":"1190","1225":"1225","1223":"1223","1221":"1221","1165":"1165","1164":"1164","1196":"1196","before 5 October 1221":"avant 5 octobre 1221","1195":"1195","Chesterton, Cambridgeshire, England":"Chesterton, Cambridgeshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Odell, Bedfordshire, England":"Odell, Bedfordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Cosford, Suffolk, England":"Cosford, Suffolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lors